  "issue_title": "Dashboard services table only shows core and llm",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nThe system dashboard on port `3080` does not show the full running service set. It currently reports only `core` and `llm` in the Services table, even when the broader GeniePod stack is running.\n\n## Current behavior\n\n- Open `http://<jetson>:3080`\n- Services table shows only:\n  - `core`\n  - `llm`\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nThe dashboard should show all relevant GeniePod services and their current status/latency where available, including services such as:\n\n- `genie-ai-runtime` / configured LLM backend\n- `genie-core`\n- `genie-api`\n- `genie-health`\n- `genie-governor`\n- `genie-mqtt`\n- `genie-audio`\n- `genie-whisper`\n- `genie-wakeword`\n- `homeassistant` when installed/enabled\n\n## Context\n\nAfter the runtime/startup fixes, the stack can be healthy and running, but the `3080` dashboard still gives an incomplete service view. This makes it harder to verify startup and diagnose missing services from the UI.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Dashboard Services table includes the deployed GeniePod service set, not only `core` and `llm`\n- Missing, disabled, inactive, failed, and healthy services are distinguishable\n- The UI remains usable when optional services are not installed\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-18T07:31:12.000Z",
